01:42.728 --> 01:44.396
- You know what? I think I got room.

01:45.397 --> 01:46.481
I used to valet.

01:47.232 --> 01:48.233
- Fuck!

01:48.233 --> 01:49.359
JULIO:
I wasn't a valet.

01:49.359 --> 01:50.903
Why the fuck did I say that?

01:50.903 --> 01:52.321
♪ Baby, what's happenin'? ♪

01:52.321 --> 01:53.572
♪ DD, got the juice ♪

01:53.572 --> 01:55.490
♪ Black is the Captain,
G is the future ♪

01:55.490 --> 01:57.576
♪ Eastside shooter ♪

01:58.035 --> 01:59.244
I got this.

01:59.786 --> 02:02.664
♪ Other niggas hate
'cause they can't fuck with us ♪

02:02.664 --> 02:04.750
You got it, you got it, you got it.
You got it.

02:05.292 --> 02:07.085
♪ Range Rover pedal
to the floor smash out ♪

02:07.085 --> 02:08.128
[tires screech]

02:10.297 --> 02:12.466
You know what? I'll just go around.

02:14.843 --> 02:19.765
♪

02:19.765 --> 02:21.975
Ooh.
- What the fuck is he doing?

02:21.975 --> 02:24.978
- Ooh! He got the little white fence!

02:26.104 --> 02:27.105
- What the fuck?

02:27.105 --> 02:30.526
♪

02:30.526 --> 02:31.610
- Ooh, ooh, ooh.

02:34.279 --> 02:35.572
- Ooh.
- Oh, shit.

02:35.572 --> 02:37.366
- Hey, good lookin' out, fellas.

02:37.366 --> 02:39.409
[men chattering]

02:39.409 --> 02:42.412
♪

02:53.423 --> 02:57.177
♪ I Think You’ve Got Your Fools Mixed Up
by Brenton Wood playing ♪

02:57.177 --> 02:58.762
♪

02:58.762 --> 03:02.057
♪ I think you got your fools mixed up ♪

03:02.057 --> 03:04.810
JULIO:
At Hugs Not Thugs, you get a second chance

03:04.810 --> 03:06.603
to decide who you want to be.

03:07.229 --> 03:09.189
Whether you're a former gang member

03:09.189 --> 03:11.108
or previously incarcerated,

03:11.108 --> 03:15.070
we offer the resources you need
to transform your life.

03:15.821 --> 03:19.616
The system may have left you behind,
but we're here for you.

03:20.284 --> 03:23.370
And we're proud to say
we remove more tattoos

03:23.370 --> 03:25.289
than anyone else in Los Angeles.

03:26.874 --> 03:30.919
Hey, big dawg, we can wipe away
that teardrop tattoo, no problem.

03:33.255 --> 03:35.382
Look, check it out,
we offer free legal counseling,

03:35.382 --> 03:37.801
solar panel installation classes.

03:37.801 --> 03:39.636
Oh, and here's the founder.

03:40.888 --> 03:42.389
Hey, Minister Payne.

03:42.389 --> 03:44.600
This is Fabian.
He's thinking about joining the program.

03:44.600 --> 03:46.059
- What's up, big dawg?

03:46.059 --> 03:48.770
- "What's up" is we just found out
Sir Richard Branson

03:48.770 --> 03:52.900
is making a generous donation
in the amount of $10,000.

03:52.900 --> 03:54.526
- Oh, good.

03:54.526 --> 03:57.196
- Cheapskate motherfucker
spends billions of dollars

03:57.196 --> 03:58.655
going up into space,

03:58.655 --> 04:01.200
barely gives us enough money
for making rent.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.328
Richard, please, throw down
a few more pennies

04:04.328 --> 04:05.913
from the troposphere.

04:05.913 --> 04:07.581
Astronaut son of a bitch!

04:07.581 --> 04:09.541
Very nice to meet you, Fabian.

04:09.541 --> 04:10.542
Welcome.

04:12.211 --> 04:13.921
Space Knight motherfucker!

04:15.005 --> 04:16.507
- That fool's a minister?

04:16.507 --> 04:19.676
- [clicks tongue]
He's a Unitarian Universalist.

04:19.676 --> 04:21.803
Those fools are like hippies but angry.

04:22.471 --> 04:24.348
Oh, yeah, can't believe
I forgot to mention.

04:25.015 --> 04:26.266
As a bonus for signing up,

04:26.975 --> 04:29.019
all new Huggers get a free mug.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.396
So what do you say, big dawg?

04:32.397 --> 04:34.024
Ready to make a better life for yourself?

04:35.776 --> 04:37.861
- [sighs] Imma be honest with you.

04:37.861 --> 04:39.696
I don't think this shit's for me, bro.

04:40.155 --> 04:42.157
- Listen, I get it, big dawg.

04:42.157 --> 04:43.742
I know what the street life is like.

04:43.742 --> 04:45.577
- What you know about street life?

04:45.577 --> 04:48.205
You look like you got
a season pass to Disneyland.

04:48.205 --> 04:50.707
- Nah, fool, I grew up in these streets.

04:50.707 --> 04:52.793
And believe me, I've seen some shit.

04:53.585 --> 04:57.297
♪ hard rock music playing ♪

04:57.297 --> 05:00.217
I was cruising through the neighborhood
on my new wheels,

05:00.217 --> 05:03.804
just chillin',
when all of a sudden this car pulled up.

05:03.804 --> 05:08.308
♪ ominous music playing ♪

05:08.308 --> 05:09.560
But I didn't panic.

05:10.018 --> 05:12.855
I instinctively maneuvered out of the way.

05:14.106 --> 05:15.607
My homie Brian was there.

05:16.191 --> 05:18.652
So I asked him, "What's going on?"

05:18.652 --> 05:22.614
And he tells me,
"Your cousin's drug deal went awry."

05:22.614 --> 05:26.743
[gunshots]

05:26.743 --> 05:29.997
♪

05:29.997 --> 05:31.290
- Oh, shit, Julio?

05:32.374 --> 05:33.625
What's crackin'?

05:34.293 --> 05:36.461
- 'Sup, Luis? Just chillin'.

05:37.296 --> 05:38.589
Kinda scared.

05:38.589 --> 05:40.340
- Are you fucking roller skating?

05:40.340 --> 05:43.010
- Well, it's actually
aggressive roller blading.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.179
- Damn, fool,
somehow that sounds even gayer.

05:45.179 --> 05:46.555
[Luis laughs]

05:46.555 --> 05:48.015
Hey, say hi to my tía for me, alright?

05:48.015 --> 05:50.434
And don't give her any problems
or I'll beat your ass.

05:50.434 --> 05:51.435
[gun cocks]
[tires screeching]

05:51.435 --> 05:52.978
- Okay, I won't.

05:53.395 --> 05:56.064
And then I said,
"Thanks for not shooting me!"

05:57.357 --> 05:59.067
- Hey, no offense, my boy,

05:59.067 --> 06:01.945
but you come off
like a punk-ass bitch in that story.

06:01.945 --> 06:03.238
- That's my point.

06:03.238 --> 06:06.158
My cousin spent
the last eight years in prison.

06:06.158 --> 06:09.203
Meanwhile, I'm out here
living my best life.

06:09.203 --> 06:11.079
I even got dental insurance.

06:11.079 --> 06:13.165
Look. Check it out.

06:13.165 --> 06:14.416
Get in here.

06:14.416 --> 06:16.627
- Man, your teeth still look
pretty fucked up, though.

06:17.461 --> 06:18.837
- Yeah, but guess what?

06:18.837 --> 06:20.380
They used to be even more fucked up.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.716
Look, you're gonna do
what you're gonna do.

06:22.716 --> 06:25.844
But studies show
that the life expectancy of a gangster,

06:25.844 --> 06:28.305
on average, 24 years old.

06:29.097 --> 06:31.642
But the life expectancy
of a punk-ass bitch?

06:32.768 --> 06:34.019
76 years old.

06:35.896 --> 06:39.691
♪

06:39.691 --> 06:41.610
Orientation is at 10:00 tomorrow.

06:41.610 --> 06:43.070
Don't be late.

06:43.070 --> 06:44.238
There's gonna be orange juice.

06:44.238 --> 06:46.448
[tires screeching]
[rock song playing over car stereo]

06:46.448 --> 06:50.118
♪

06:52.371 --> 06:53.664
Maggie?

06:58.001 --> 07:00.045
[music stops]
[cell phone rings]

07:00.045 --> 07:03.131
- Oh, hey, Julio, what's up?
You need something?

07:03.131 --> 07:04.675
- Did you just steal my car?

07:04.675 --> 07:05.843
MAGGIE [over phone]:
Excuse me?

07:05.843 --> 07:07.302
Don't use that word with me.

07:07.302 --> 07:10.931
My car broke down,
so I borrowed yours to run errands.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.182
I'll bring it back tonight, beggar.

07:12.182 --> 07:14.309
- When did I say you could borrow my car?

07:14.309 --> 07:15.853
- Remember when you left
your spare key at my house

07:15.853 --> 07:17.813
that one time on accident?
- Yeah?

07:17.813 --> 07:19.606
MAGGIE:
Then do the math, bitch.

07:19.606 --> 07:22.484
Oh, by the way,
your check engine light is on.

07:22.484 --> 07:25.362
Julio, that's dangerous.
I should be the one who is mad.

07:26.572 --> 07:27.573
You know what, actually?

07:28.907 --> 07:31.368
How fucking dare you?
You put me in danger.

07:31.368 --> 07:33.453
Why the fuck would you do that to me?

07:33.453 --> 07:35.497
- Well, bring it back then.
I gotta pick up Luis.

07:36.290 --> 07:37.791
- No shit.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.585
They're letting your cousin out?

07:39.585 --> 07:41.753
Man, the prison system is stupid.

07:41.753 --> 07:44.006
- Actually, he's gonna
stay with us for a while.

07:44.590 --> 07:46.133
Imma help that fool get his life together.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.509
Take that fool under my wing.

07:47.509 --> 07:48.719
[Maggie sighs deeply]

07:48.719 --> 07:51.471
- You know, Julio,
you really are the nicest ex I have.

07:51.471 --> 07:54.725
That's why I thought
you'd be cool if I borrowed your car.

07:54.725 --> 07:56.727
But if you want me
to bring it back, that's fine.

07:56.727 --> 07:57.978
- Thank you.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.646
- I'll just call another ex.

07:59.646 --> 08:01.648
Maybe Carlos.

08:02.357 --> 08:03.817
We're talking again.

08:04.860 --> 08:07.154
♪

08:07.154 --> 08:09.823
BEN [over microphone]:
The Black man is the original man.

08:09.823 --> 08:13.911
And Latinos, Asians, and Native Americans
are all our children.

08:14.578 --> 08:16.747
Now some of you make me proud,

08:16.747 --> 08:18.957
but some of you are not men.

08:18.957 --> 08:21.168
You may have the body of a man,

08:21.168 --> 08:23.212
but possess a child's will.

08:23.712 --> 08:25.380
Stand up for the word of the Lord.

08:26.006 --> 08:27.341
A storm is comin'!

08:27.341 --> 08:30.177
♪

08:55.452 --> 08:56.662
- Sorry I'm late!

08:57.162 --> 08:58.872
LUIS:
Damn, you run slow.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.791
You should have brought
your roller skates.

09:01.250 --> 09:02.709
- They were roller blades.

09:03.335 --> 09:04.711
It's different.

09:12.928 --> 09:16.014
- So... where's your ride at, primo?

09:16.014 --> 09:17.683
- I let my homegirl borrow it.

09:18.267 --> 09:20.686
But don't worry, I got you.

09:20.686 --> 09:22.271
I'll call us an Uber.

09:22.271 --> 09:24.064
Uber is like the taxi of the future.

09:24.064 --> 09:25.649
- [mocking Julio]
Uber is like the taxi of the future.

09:25.649 --> 09:27.192
I know what Uber is, pendejo.

09:27.192 --> 09:28.902
Eh, talking to me like that.

09:31.154 --> 09:32.364
Actually, they have Uber in prison.

09:32.990 --> 09:35.117
Yeah. His name is Thumper.

09:35.117 --> 09:37.411
And if you give him a pack of cigarettes,
he'll carry you around, like, hey.

09:37.911 --> 09:38.912
It's pretty convenient.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.790
Damn, my boy.
I haven't seen you forever.

09:42.749 --> 09:43.834
Hey, for real though,

09:43.834 --> 09:45.669
why does your body still look 19

09:45.669 --> 09:48.505
but your face looks 56, fool?

09:48.505 --> 09:50.090
[Luis laughs]
- Yup.

09:50.090 --> 09:52.176
- You got Edward James Olmos' face.

09:53.969 --> 09:56.096
- Welcome back, fool. I missed you too.

09:56.096 --> 09:57.097
- Ehh.

09:57.890 --> 09:59.474
Don't be nasty, alright? We're family.

10:00.225 --> 10:01.268
I don't get down like that.

10:02.352 --> 10:03.937
- Cool. Yeah. Okay.

10:04.855 --> 10:06.064
♪

10:06.064 --> 10:08.192
[indistinct chatter in Spanish]

10:08.192 --> 10:12.321
♪

10:21.413 --> 10:23.916
[chatter continues]

10:35.177 --> 10:37.679
♪

10:38.263 --> 10:40.015
AIDEN:
I'm gonna beat your ass, Michael!

10:40.015 --> 10:42.100
- Hey, hey, Aiden.
Come here.

10:43.560 --> 10:45.229
Gotta be more careful, alright?

10:45.229 --> 10:47.523
You almost just broke
this photo of me and my mom.

10:47.523 --> 10:50.067
I'm gonna forgive you
because you're a little homie.

10:50.067 --> 10:53.362
But if this was a level four yard,
I would've stabbed you.

10:54.404 --> 10:55.697
You understand?

10:55.697 --> 10:57.032
- Yeah.

10:57.032 --> 10:58.408
- Okay.

10:58.408 --> 11:01.036
Now, come here. Give me a hug.
I'm your tío Luis, alright?

11:01.036 --> 11:02.371
I love you, mijo.

11:02.371 --> 11:05.123
♪

11:08.001 --> 11:11.004
♪

11:11.004 --> 11:12.506
- Julio. Julio!

11:22.975 --> 11:25.060
- Eh, who let
the Mexican Oompa Loompa in here, huh?

11:25.060 --> 11:26.270
Oompa!

11:26.270 --> 11:28.146
[kids laughing]

11:30.065 --> 11:32.067
- Hey, what's up with that tarp
I saw on the roof?

11:55.340 --> 11:56.800
ROCIO:
Yeah, teach his ass.

11:56.800 --> 11:58.760
This fool can't even build Legos.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.971
[kids laugh]
[mouths]

12:00.971 --> 12:02.181
LUIS:
It's the least I could do to repay you.

12:16.320 --> 12:18.906
- Actually, I have some exciting news.

12:18.906 --> 12:20.616
I've kinda become a big deal
at Hugs Not Thugs

12:20.616 --> 12:24.328
which is now the fifth largest
gang rehabilitation center in Los Angeles.

12:25.037 --> 12:28.207
Anyway, I pulled a few strings
and I was able to get Luis a spot.

12:28.207 --> 12:30.834
Imma be your case manager,
help you find a new career.

12:30.834 --> 12:33.170
- You can case manage these nuts, homie.

12:33.170 --> 12:34.213
[laughter]

12:35.631 --> 12:37.966
- Yeah, Julio, you're the one
who needs to get your life together.

12:37.966 --> 12:40.969
Like, you waste all your money
buying dumbass comic books

12:40.969 --> 12:42.804
and I literally saw CDs in your room.

12:42.804 --> 12:45.724
Like, who the fuck pays for music, idiot?

12:45.724 --> 12:47.476
- I like physical media.

12:47.476 --> 12:49.603
- Yeah, Mom, how come
you let him stay here for free?

12:49.603 --> 12:52.147
You made me start paying rent
after my quinceañera.

12:52.147 --> 12:54.233
You made me pay for my quinceañera.

13:00.864 --> 13:02.199
- Ah, nah, don't worry about me, tía.

13:02.199 --> 13:03.825
I can find a job on my own.

13:03.825 --> 13:05.953
Plus, I just got out, you know,
I wanna kick it first.

13:19.675 --> 13:23.345
- Hmm. So I guess
if he wants to stay here,

13:23.345 --> 13:25.764
then he has to join Hugs Not Thugs.

13:31.228 --> 13:35.858
♪ relaxing music playing ♪

13:48.495 --> 13:49.621
[beeps]

13:50.914 --> 13:51.915
[steady beep]

13:51.915 --> 13:56.670
♪

13:56.670 --> 13:58.088
JULIO:
Hurry up, we're gonna be late.

14:03.302 --> 14:04.344
- Where's your ride at?

14:04.887 --> 14:06.513
- You took my car to San Diego?

14:06.513 --> 14:08.473
- I thought you needed
to run a few errands.

14:08.473 --> 14:10.642
MAGGIE [over phone]:
People can run errands in San Diego.

14:10.642 --> 14:12.394
Don't be racist.

14:12.394 --> 14:14.688
- What the fuck kind of errands
are you running in San Diego?

14:14.688 --> 14:16.356
MAGGIE: None of your business
what kind of errands.

14:16.356 --> 14:19.109
Always so nosy.
Respect my boundaries. Bye.

14:19.109 --> 14:20.110
[line beeps]

14:25.532 --> 14:28.577
- She's your ex?
Ah, she's using you, bro.

14:28.577 --> 14:30.204
Look at it closely.

14:30.204 --> 14:32.539
- We still hook up. Sometimes.

14:33.081 --> 14:36.251
- Hey. Doesn't that make
your boyfriend jealous?

14:36.710 --> 14:37.836
I feel for him.

14:41.298 --> 14:42.758
MINISTER PAYNE:
You should all be proud

14:42.758 --> 14:44.676
to be sitting here today,

14:44.676 --> 14:47.137
mainly because it means
you've escaped

14:47.137 --> 14:51.141
the corrupt for-profit
prison industrial complex

14:51.141 --> 14:54.603
put in place
by our racist, classist government.

14:56.313 --> 15:00.025
But also because
you've taken the first step

15:00.025 --> 15:03.070
towards gaining control of your life.

15:03.070 --> 15:07.324
Now, the second step is a test

15:07.324 --> 15:10.410
of great spiritual and mental fortitude.

15:11.578 --> 15:12.913
You must bake

15:14.581 --> 15:16.124
a delicious cupcake.

15:16.124 --> 15:18.085
[confused chatter]
MAN: What? What?

15:18.085 --> 15:20.170
- Yo. Julio, what the fuck, man?

15:20.170 --> 15:22.714
Thought you said I'd be designing
solar panels and shit.

15:22.714 --> 15:25.050
- Hey, dawg, the only way
we can afford that program

15:25.050 --> 15:28.053
is by selling these cupcakes
to local supermarkets.

15:28.053 --> 15:30.639
- People love buying cupcakes
from ex-gang members.

15:30.639 --> 15:32.474
The only nonprofit that sells

15:32.474 --> 15:34.434
more sweets than us
are the Girl Scouts.

15:34.434 --> 15:38.230
If the Girl Scouts ever start
getting face tattoos, we're fucked.

15:38.230 --> 15:40.732
- Hey, this is like
some exploitation shit.

15:40.732 --> 15:42.234
It's like prison labor, homies.

15:42.734 --> 15:44.111
We oughta unionize.

15:44.111 --> 15:45.237
[all chatter in agreement]

15:45.863 --> 15:48.156
[banging pot]

15:48.824 --> 15:51.326
CHEF PERCY WILLIAMS:
Shut the fuck up!

15:52.452 --> 15:53.579
♪ march music plays ♪

15:53.579 --> 15:56.665
Now I know why you bitches
don't wanna bake cupcakes.

15:56.665 --> 15:59.168
See, it ain't got nothing to do
with the pink apron.

16:00.169 --> 16:01.670
It's 'cause deep down inside,

16:02.588 --> 16:04.423
you motherfuckers is afraid to fail.

16:05.382 --> 16:06.884
'Cause this ain't your world.

16:07.426 --> 16:08.760
This is my world.

16:09.428 --> 16:10.596
Cupcake world.

16:11.555 --> 16:14.725
I'm a cupcake girl in a cupcake world.

16:14.725 --> 16:19.271
And you will not come in here
and disrespect my cupcake world.

16:20.522 --> 16:21.523
Bitch.

16:22.149 --> 16:25.194
- Thank you, Chef Percy Williams.

16:25.194 --> 16:27.029
He started out just like all of you

16:27.029 --> 16:28.989
then he went through our culinary program,

16:28.989 --> 16:33.452
and now he is
a gourmet pastry chef at Sprinkles.

16:33.952 --> 16:35.954
- Well, I'll fuck with some Sprinkles.

16:35.954 --> 16:38.165
